There’s nothing Keke “Keep a Job” Palmer can’t do. With an impressive 75 acting credits, an Emmy, and five NAACP Image Awards, she’s more than proven that she’s here to make an impact. “I can't change everything,” she tells @glamourmag editor @ru_wolle. “I’m not able to fix and save the world, even though I wish that I could, but I can do a little bit from where I am by exposing, supporting, and giving them access—offering the same kind of opportunities that were offered to me.”

At the link in bio, Palmer opens up about the people who have inspired her, the responsibility she feels about being the first at many things, and what it’s like to be an Instagram icon.

The 2022 Glamour Beauty Awards are here!!! 💄💜 ✨

It’s been two (!!!) years of strides and setbacks, and although we haven’t completely figured out what life looks like post pandemic, our beauty routines have adjusted accordingly. 

This year’s #GlamourBeautyAwards is dedicated to defining beauty on your own terms, whether that means rediscovering basic products you may have put down during the last two years or playing with bold TikTok trends like hyper-bright blush or colored graphic eyeliner. Whatever beauty looks like for you now, we found a winning product you’ll love…264 of them to be exact. Tap the link in bio for the best beauty products of 2022.

All hail queen Meg. After creating viral comedy videos online (“hi gay,” anyone?) to literally having scenes written for her in HBO’s Emmy-winning series “Hacks,” Megan Stalter feels prepared for what’s next—and that’s starring in her own Netflix series written by Lena Dunham. For Glamour’s July cover, read as the ‘Too Much’ star shares the protection method she developed in her drama club days, the career she would have if she wasn’t a comedian, and more. Tap the link in bio to read the full story.

latestPosts.caption: The July Fourth weekend turned tragic as torrential downpours quickly turned into deadly floods across central Texas, taking the lives of dozens of children and adults. Even as search and rescue missions are underway, the official death toll is still unknown, and there's more rain on the horizon. If you're looking for a way to help the communities directly impacted by the devastating floods as they repair and rebuild, here are some organizations providing on-the-ground resources. See the full list at the link in bio.
